2500|$|For a {{persistent}} world {{to maintain a}} stable economy, a balance must be struck between currency sources and sinks. Generally, games possess numerous sources of new currency for players to earn. [...] However, some possess no effective [...] "sinks", or methods of removing currency from circulation. [...] If other factors remain constant, greater currency supply weakens the buying power of a given amount; {{a process known as}} inflation. [...] In practice, this results in constantly rising prices for traded commodities. [...] With the proper balance of growth in player <b>base,</b> <b>currency</b> sources, and sinks, a virtual economy could remain stable indefinitely.|$|E
