40|$|Momentum in {{developed}} countries' {{stock market index}} returns can be exploited to form portfolios of excess returns on foreign currencies as relatively high past foreign stock market returns signal a foreign currency appreciation. Two risk factors extracted from the stock index momentum <b>based</b> <b>currency</b> portfolio returns explain more than 80 percent of their cross-sectional variation. In contrast to currency risk factors constructed from forward discount sorted currency portfolios, these risk factors {{are not related to}} business cycle or liquidity risk. But high currency risk premia are associated with relatively deep financial integration and a high level of risk sharing. Currency returns, financial integration, momentum, risk premia, UIP...|$|R
